By the Law of Cosines on triangle $AOP,$
\[AP^2 = AO^2 + OP^2 - 2 \cdot AO \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOP = R^2 + OP^2 - 2R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOP.\]Similarly,
\begin{align*}
BP^2 &= R^2 + OP^2 - 2R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle BOP, \\
CP^2 &= R^2 + OP^2 - 2R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle COP.
\end{align*}Then
\begin{align*}
AB^2 + AP^2 + BP^2 &= AB^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 2R \cdot OP (\cos \angle AOP + \cos \angle BOP) \\
&= AB^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 2R \cdot OP \cdot 2 \cos \angle AOB \cdot \cos \angle BOC \\
&= AB^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOB \cdot \cos \angle BOC.
\end{align*}Similarly,
\begin{align*}
AC^2 + AP^2 + CP^2 &= AC^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOC \cdot \cos \angle BOC, \\
BC^2 + BP^2 + CP^2 &= BC^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle BOC \cdot \cos \angle COA.
\end{align*}Since these three expressions are equal,
\[AB^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOB \cdot \cos \angle BOC = AC^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOC \cdot \cos \angle BOC = BC^2 + 2R^2 + 2OP^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle BOC \cdot \cos \angle COA.\]This simplifies to
\[AB^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOB \cdot \cos \angle BOC = AC^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle AOC \cdot \cos \angle BOC = BC^2 - 4R \cdot OP \cdot \cos \angle BOC \cdot \cos \angle COA.\]Since $\cos \angle AOB = \cos \angle AOC = \cos \angle BOC,$ we can cancel these terms, to get
\[AB^2 = AC^2 = BC^2.\]This means triangle $ABC$ is equilateral.

Let $s$ be the side length of the equilateral triangle.  Then
\[AB^2 + AP^2 + BP^2 = AC^2 + AP^2 + CP^2 = BC^2 + BP^2 + CP^2 = s^2 + AP^2 + BP^2 = s^2 + CP^2 + AP^2 = s^2 + BP^2 + CP^2.\]Hence, the common value is $\boxed{s^2 + AP^2 + BP^2}.$

